node.text:
There’s a NEW video on the tube that we’ve poured all of our heart into ❤️⁣
⁣
I was raised by the most incredible parents. Both refugees to Canada from Afghanistan, and growing up they fed us plenty of delicious Afghan food. With what’s been going on there, I’ve been feeling a strong desire to do something. So I thought, what if I connect you with the beauty of the Afghan culture and its people through its cuisine? Plus, you’ll “meet” my parents for the first time in this video 🥰⁣
⁣
This video features 5 traditional Afghan recipes I grew up enjoying, plus we’ve published an additional 4 new recipes on the blog that we couldn’t fit into the video. That’s 9 new recipes! 🇦🇫⁣
⁣
All of the revenue from this video will be donated to 3 non-profit organizations helping the Afghan people right now. Every view helps 🙏 and thanks in advance if you choose to share it with friends and family, you’re amazing! 🤗⁣ video link is in profile 📽
⁣
 #afghanistan #vegan #plantbased

node.text: Hey friends, there’s a new TeaTime Tuesday video up about overthinking and worrying, something I’ve been doing even moreso of these last few days. In the video we explore the strategy I’ve been using to deal with it. Curious if you find yourself overthinking as well, and if there are any strategies you use in your own life that helps? I’d love to know about it. In the meantime, the video link is in profile 💛

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Sadia Badiei, BSc Dietetics on August 16, 2021. May be an image of 3 people and text that says 'Canada, 1996'.

node.text:
My heart aches for Afghanistan. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
I’m the youngest of 3 girls, a daughter to Afghan parents who risked their lives and fled from their beloved homeland during the war of 1979. My mum was 9 months pregnant with their first child.⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Prior to that, Afghanistan was a beautiful country. From the stories my parents share, it was a forward-thinking nation. My mum went to school, got to choose who she wanted to marry, and I’m still in awe of their good fashion sense back then.⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣⁣
But now, the taliban have seized control. This is the start of the darkest times for the families and especially girls and women in Afghanistan. They will be stripped of their rights, forced into marriages, forbidden to leave the house without a male, forced to wear burqas, forbidden to go to school. Can you even imagine what that must be like?⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣
If my parents hadn’t have made it out of the country, me and my sisters would very likely be with those girls today. Afraid for our lives, afraid for our children, and afraid for our futures.⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣
I hope countries continue to offer safe passage and asylum for Afghan families. They have potential like any other. They desire freedom and safety like any other. They are good, caring, loving, generous people.⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣⁣
I hope Afghanistan can return to the beautiful country it once was. It deserves better. Its people deserve better.

node.text:
Has it felt like a looooong Wednesday for anyone else? Coffee is seriously the life force keeping me going right now 😅

If you enjoy a good ol’ cup of brew but don’t have any coffee apparatus to make it, this cold brew coffee recipe is for you! All you need: coffee beans, a jar, and some cheesecloth (or nut milk bag). 

You can make a big batch of the concentrate, and then you’ve got coffee-on-demand for the next week 🕺🏻 We served it with a homemade vanilla #vegan coffee cream too 🤤 

Full recipe link in profile 🌞 #coffee #humpday #coldbrew #plantbased

node.text: This granola brings together two of my favourite things: granola and chocolate 🍫 I usually top my smoothie bowls and yogurt with crunchy granola, but for a super-fast breakfast, granola with plant-milk or yogurt and some fresh fruit is the way to go 🍓 Meal prep it this weekend to enjoy it all week! Have you made any of our granola recipes yet? Which is your favourite? Recipe link in profile 🌞  #vegan #plantbased #breakfast #mealprep

node.text:
We interrupt your regular programming for this appreciation post. Thanks for being here. Thanks for reading this. Thanks for watching our videos and trying our recipes. Thanks to the 1000s of you who’ve left comments and ratings on our recipes. How we got so darn lucky with this PUL family of ours I’ll never know.⁣
⁣
In case you missed it, when we transferred our website from the old one to the new one, we couldn’t transfer over the comments with it. Comments and ratings really help others know which recipes were enjoyed, and so it helps a lot! If it’s not a huge ask, and if you have a moment to spare, could we invite you to share your review on any PUL recipe you’ve tried? It’d be so appreciated💕 I’ll leave our website link in profile 🌱⁣
⁣
Sending our thanks, a virtual hug, and a cupcake if we could 😋 #recipes #vegan #plantbased

node.text: Fancy something fancy this weekend? 🥂 This peach thyme iced tea is a divine way to use up any super ripe peaches you might have. If you don’t have any peaches, it’s an excuse to go buy some 😉 and nectarines work just as well too. It’s easily my favourite iced tea recipe to date 🍑 full recipe with the link in profile ☀️ #vegan #plantbased #summer

node.text: Hello beautiful green smoothie 😏  I often use frozen bananas in my smoothies to make them cool and frothy, but we’ve gotten loads of requests for banana-less smoothies, and this one won’t disappoint! It’s made pleasantly sweet from the frozen pineapple 🍍 and refreshingly cool from the frozen cucumber 🥒 for the full recipe breakdown, check the link in profile 💚 #vegan #smoothie #plantbased

node.text:
There's a NEW video on the tube! 🥰⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Moving away from Canada is not something I ever thought I'd do. I moved to the Netherlands for love, but it came with a considerable amount of heartache in missing my family, along with an ongoing nagging feeling that I would need to eventually learn Dutch. I'll say frankly that language learning is not an interest of mine, but in order to be able to continue to stay in the Netherlands, I was required to learn a basic level of Dutch. I was given a generous few years by the government to learn the language, but silly me kept postponing studying. I think in my heart I kept thinking Robin and I would move back to Canada before the deadline approached. But that didn't happen. And the cherry on top: the deadline even got pushed up 5 months, so I had only about 1 week to cram in learning as much Dutch as I possibly could 🇳🇱⁣
⁣
This is that story. Plus the video features the incredible @nathanieldrew_ 🕺🏻 Video link in profile! 🎥 ⁣⁣
